"script": "Imagine an animal you could freeze, boil, and shoot into space, and it would just shrug it off. That's the tardigrade, a creature smaller than a grain of sand. When conditions turn deadly, it curls into a ball and squeezes nearly all the water out of its body, dropping into a state between life and death. In this form, it survives temperatures near absolute zero and radiation that would vaporize you. Scientists have even revived ones frozen for thirty years. Add a single drop of water, and it simply wakes up and walks away.",
